594
00:19:16,503 --> 00:19:18,028
that aims to eliminate

595
00:19:18,078 --> 00:19:19,316
the budget deficit

596
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:20,703
and shrink the state.

597
00:19:21,241 --> 00:19:22,603
A shrunken state

598
00:19:22,641 --> 00:19:23,766
in my experience

599
00:19:23,853 --> 00:19:25,491
is a disempowered state;

600
00:19:25,553 --> 00:19:27,241
that lacks the capacity

601
00:19:27,316 --> 00:19:29,591
to offer smart state solution.

602
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:33,225
And the real problem is this:

603
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:34,975
The public sector

604
00:19:35,025 --> 00:19:37,025
becoming more important,

605
00:19:37,063 --> 00:19:38,900
not less important,

606
00:19:38,925 --> 00:19:40,613
to innovation strategies

607
00:19:40,688 --> 00:19:42,600
because innovation itself

608
00:19:42,663 --> 00:19:43,163
now

609
00:19:43,213 --> 00:19:44,413
is evolving

610
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:46,325
from a narrow conception

611
00:19:46,363 --> 00:19:47,963
around science and technology

612
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,488
to a much wider conception

613
00:19:50,563 --> 00:19:52,525
of societal innovation.

614
00:19:52,725 --> 00:19:54,000
When we think of

615
00:19:54,025 --> 00:19:56,375
innovation in key sectors

616
00:19:56,425 --> 00:19:57,825
like healthcare

617
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,075
socialcare,

618
00:19:59,150 --> 00:20:00,338
education

619
00:20:00,388 --> 00:20:01,225
energy,

620
00:20:01,275 --> 00:20:02,263
transport,

621
00:20:02,325 --> 00:20:05,025
agrifood or the built environment,

622
00:20:05,075 --> 00:20:07,188
in all these sectors

623
00:20:07,238 --> 00:20:08,863
the public sector

624
00:20:08,938 --> 00:20:10,838
makes a major contribution

625
00:20:10,888 --> 00:20:12,663
to smart, sustainable

626
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:14,138
and inclusive growth.

627
00:20:14,188 --> 00:20:16,363
These are sectors what I call

628
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:18,450
the societal challenge sectors

629
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:21,463
in which the State looms large

630
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,713
in every sector.

631
00:20:22,813 --> 00:20:23,800
And therefore it is -

632
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,488
it is counterproductive

633
00:20:25,538 --> 00:20:27,625
to assume that the public sector

634
00:20:27,663 --> 00:20:30,575
can be displaced from these sectors

635
00:20:30,613 --> 00:20:32,838
when it plays such a major role.

